1
00:00:04,138 --> 00:00:07,575
(Minseok) ⟨I was chased out of a South Korean chaebol family after being accused of embezzlement→

2
00:00:08,175 --> 00:00:12,613
In despair, I met Momoko, a doctor at the clinic⟩

3
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:16,617
⟨Many problems befall him as his feelings for her grow⟩

4
00:00:16,684 --> 00:00:18,619
⟨but…⟩

5
00:00:18,686 --> 00:00:20,621
I love Momoko.

6
00:00:20,688 --> 00:00:23,624
(Momoko) I love you too.

7
00:00:23,691 --> 00:00:26,627
(Minseok) ``There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times.''

8
00:00:26,694 --> 00:00:30,131
The words that made me meet Momoko again.

9
00:00:30,197 --> 00:00:34,135
⟨We spent some irreplaceable time together⟩

10
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:36,137
⟨but…⟩

11
00:00:36,203 --> 00:00:40,141
(Momoko) I think now is an important time for my work.

12
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:41,642
Let's break up.

13
00:00:41,709 --> 00:00:45,146
(Minseok) ⟨Momoko suddenly broke up with me⟩

14
00:00:45,212 --> 00:00:48,649
(Eri) He will lose his favorite job at the hotel.

15
00:00:48,716 --> 00:00:52,153
Please, please break up with him.

16
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:55,156
(Minseok) ⟨“I don’t want to give up like this.” That’s what I thought…⟩

17
00:00:55,222 --> 00:00:57,224
(Eri) Minseok-san.

18
00:01:00,227 --> 00:01:02,229
(Minseok) Inri-san.

19
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:07,101
>> I have something to tell you.

20
00:01:07,168 --> 00:01:09,170
Let's go.

21
00:01:11,172 --> 00:01:14,608
(Minseok) Sorry, we're talking now...

22
00:01:14,675 --> 00:01:17,611
>> Yes, but if you don't hurry, it'll be too late.

23
00:01:17,678 --> 00:01:20,114
(Minseok) No, what are you talking about?

24
00:01:20,181 --> 00:01:25,119
>> Because of you, many people will end up on the streets.

25
00:01:25,186 --> 00:01:27,188
(Minseok) What do you mean?

26
00:01:35,696 --> 00:01:44,638
(cry)

27
00:01:44,705 --> 00:01:48,142
(Eri) Your mother-in-law wanted to banish you from Fangum→

28
00:01:48,209 --> 00:01:51,145
I'm going to destroy Fangum Hotel Tokyo.

29
00:01:51,212 --> 00:01:52,646
(Minseok) Huh?

30
00:01:52,713 --> 00:01:55,649
>>To begin with, hotels in Tokyo have low profit margins→

31
00:01:55,716 --> 00:01:59,153
It's not worth keeping it alive.

32
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:01,655
(Minseok) How do you know that?

33
00:02:01,722 --> 00:02:04,592
>>My mother-in-law told me about it.

34
00:02:04,658 --> 00:02:10,164
My mother-in-law wants me and Hee-sung to get married.

35
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:13,601
(Minseok) You and your brother?

36
00:02:13,667 --> 00:02:16,604
>> If that happens, it will be as originally planned→

37
00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:20,608
A business partnership will become possible between Fungum and the Shinkai Group.

38
00:02:20,674 --> 00:02:24,111
That's not a bad thing.

39
00:02:24,178 --> 00:02:28,616
But more than anything, I feel sorry for you.

40
00:02:28,682 --> 00:02:32,186
As a childhood friend's ex-fiance.

41
00:02:35,189 --> 00:02:40,628
If a hotel in Tokyo is cut down, all employees will be fired.

42
00:02:40,694 --> 00:02:43,631
But now if you quit the hotel →

43
00:02:43,697 --> 00:02:46,634
I'm sure your mother-in-law will also dissuade you.

44
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:52,139
Would you stand down for the sake of your employees?

45
00:02:52,206 --> 00:02:56,143
You are more than my own happiness →

46
00:02:56,210 --> 00:03:00,147
Because he is a person who prioritizes the happiness of those around him.

47
00:03:00,214 --> 00:03:02,650
But if I were →

48
00:03:02,716 --> 00:03:07,154
You can help those around you and yourself.

49
00:03:13,661 --> 00:03:18,666
(door chime)

50
00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:22,603
(Takuto) Yay!

51
00:03:22,670 --> 00:03:25,606
(Kyoko) Momoko~｡ (Momoko) Huh, big sister!

52
00:03:25,673 --> 00:03:27,608
what happened? (Kyoko) Are you home?

53
00:03:27,675 --> 00:03:31,111
(Momoko) What, did you drink? >> Yeah, just a little...

54
00:03:31,178 --> 00:03:33,113
Isn't there another one? Beer.

55
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:35,115
(Momoko) I don't drink. I don't drink.

56
00:03:35,182 --> 00:03:38,686
Sister, did you drink water? >> I don't drink beer, so...

57
00:03:40,187 --> 00:03:42,623
I was surprised at how sudden the story was.

58
00:03:42,690 --> 00:03:47,628
How you and your hotel in Tokyo can help →

59
00:03:47,695 --> 00:03:50,698
Please contact me if you want to hear it.

60
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:05,079
(Momoko) Thank you, Takuto.

61
00:04:05,145 --> 00:04:07,081
(Takuto) Uh-huh.

62
00:04:07,147 --> 00:04:10,084
Hey Momoko. (Momoko) Huh?

63
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:12,653
(Takuto) Did something happen?

64
00:04:14,655 --> 00:04:16,590
(Momoko) Nothing.

65
00:04:16,657 --> 00:04:19,593
(Takuto) I see. (Momoko) Yeah.

66
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:22,096
(Takuto) Well then, eat and sleep properly.

67
00:04:22,162 --> 00:04:24,598
(Momoko) Yeah, good night.

68
00:04:24,665 --> 00:04:26,166
(Takuto) Good night.

69
00:04:27,668 --> 00:04:31,105
(Sound of door opening and closing)

70
00:04:31,171 --> 00:04:41,115
♪～

71
00:04:41,181 --> 00:04:43,183
(Sound of turning on the light)

72
00:04:52,192 --> 00:04:54,128
(Eri) [Because of you→

73
00:04:54,194 --> 00:04:57,197
Many people will end up on the streets.]

74
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:02,636
(Momoko) [There are trees that will not fall even if they are cut 10 times]

75
00:05:02,703 --> 00:05:05,139
[Everything doesn't go as planned]

76
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:16,150
(Minseok) 《I have lost a lot of things until now》

77
00:05:21,655 --> 00:05:26,093
(Minseok) 《I don't want to lose anything anymore》

78
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:37,671
♪～

79
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:55,622
♪～

80
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:58,625
>> Their eyes are similar. (Natsume) Is that true?

81
00:05:58,692 --> 00:06:00,627
(Minseok) Good morning.

82
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:03,130
(Natsume) Ah, good morning, Deputy Manager.

83
00:06:03,197 --> 00:06:07,067
Can I have a look at it please?

84
00:06:07,134 --> 00:06:09,570
I have successfully become a father.

85
00:06:09,636 --> 00:06:12,072
(Minseok) Congratulations! (Natsume) Thank you.

86
00:06:12,139 --> 00:06:15,576
It's really cute.

87
00:06:15,642 --> 00:06:19,580
Ah, I have to earn a lot of money in order to raise my child on my own.

88
00:06:19,646 --> 00:06:22,082
Thank you for your continued support.

89
00:06:22,149 --> 00:06:24,585
(Minseok) Welcome.

90
00:06:24,651 --> 00:06:27,087
>>Ah, I want to meet you soon.

91
00:06:27,154 --> 00:06:29,089
(Staff) Welcome. (Male) Where's the restaurant?

92
00:06:29,156 --> 00:06:31,091
(Staff) The restaurant is over here...｡

93
00:06:31,158 --> 00:06:32,593
I got it….

94
00:06:32,659 --> 00:06:34,661
We will keep your luggage.

95
00:06:36,663 --> 00:06:39,099
(Inri) [If the hotels in Tokyo are cut down →

96
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:41,602
All employees will be fired

97
00:06:41,668 --> 00:06:49,676
(footsteps)

98
00:06:51,678 --> 00:06:54,114
(Minseok) Manager.

99
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:56,116
(Mizushima) What's wrong?

100
00:06:56,183 --> 00:06:58,118
(Minseok) I have a favor to ask of you.

101
00:06:58,185 --> 00:06:59,686
(Mizushima) Huh?

102
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:08,061
Yes, that one suits you better after all.

103
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:09,563
Me too →

104
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:12,065
“Why don’t you graduate from being a bellman soon?”→

105
00:07:12,132 --> 00:07:14,067
That's what I was trying to say.

106
00:07:14,134 --> 00:07:16,570
(Minseok) Thank you.

107
00:07:16,637 --> 00:07:18,639
>> Please.

108
00:07:22,643 --> 00:07:26,079
This is a summary of the current business situation.

109
00:07:26,146 --> 00:07:29,082
We are still fully booked due to inbound demand →

110
00:07:29,149 --> 00:07:32,085
Weddings, large meetings, etc. →

111
00:07:32,152 --> 00:07:36,156
Demand for events with high profit margins is declining.

112
00:07:37,658 --> 00:07:39,092
(Minseok) Manager.

113
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:40,594
>> Yes.

114
00:07:40,661 --> 00:07:42,663
(Minseok) Could you give me some time?

115
00:07:47,167 --> 00:07:52,673
(Minseok) 《I hope this becomes a hotel worth keeping for the head office》

116
00:07:56,176 --> 00:07:58,178
(Minseok) 《I'm sure...》

117
00:08:02,182 --> 00:08:04,051
(Takuto) This is what I created →

118
00:08:04,117 --> 00:08:07,120
This is a satellite plan for Kazami Clinic.

119
00:08:09,623 --> 00:08:13,560
The role of Kazami Clinic, which has supported local medical care, will remain the same →

120
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:17,064
Treatment and home visits for patients in the chronic stage are also available →

121
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:19,066
You can do it as before.

122
00:08:19,132 --> 00:08:21,068
(Kazami) Good.

123
00:08:21,134 --> 00:08:25,072
We have patients who have relied on us for a long time.

124
00:08:25,138 --> 00:08:27,074
(Takuto) Yes.

125
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:32,579
But this place...

126
00:08:32,646 --> 00:08:34,581
By turning it into a rehabilitation facility →

127
00:08:34,648 --> 00:08:37,084
It is necessary to stabilize management.

128
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:40,087
>> Yeah...｡

129
00:08:40,153 --> 00:08:44,591
Then, what about the children's cafeteria?

130
00:08:44,658 --> 00:08:47,160
It's already over.

131
00:08:49,663 --> 00:08:51,665
(Peach) Dean.

132
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:56,169
>> Huh... Yeah.

133
00:08:58,171 --> 00:09:01,608
To protect something→

134
00:09:01,675 --> 00:09:05,545
Sometimes you have to give up.

135
00:09:05,612 --> 00:09:08,048
(Takuto) Sorry, Director.

136
00:09:08,115 --> 00:09:10,050
>> What are you talking about?

137
00:09:10,117 --> 00:09:14,121
Thank you for everything, Takuto-kun.

138
00:09:15,622 --> 00:09:20,561
Okay, let's proceed now.

139
00:09:20,627 --> 00:09:22,629
(Takuto) Yes.

140
00:09:30,137 --> 00:09:32,139
(Minseok) Manager.

141
00:09:34,141 --> 00:09:37,077
Please read this. (Mizushima) Huh?

142
00:09:37,144 --> 00:09:39,580
(Minseok) This is a business strategy proposal. (Mizushima) Oh.

143
00:09:39,646 --> 00:09:41,581
Have you done it yet?

144
00:09:41,648 --> 00:09:43,583
Read carefully later...

145
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:45,585
(Minseok) Please read it now. >> Yes?

146
00:09:45,652 --> 00:09:48,088
(Minseok) Please. >> What's wrong?

147
00:09:48,155 --> 00:09:49,589
(Minseok) I don't have time.

148
00:09:49,656 --> 00:09:51,658
>> What do you mean?

149
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:56,163
(Minseok) I want to see results quickly.

150
00:09:57,664 --> 00:10:00,100
(Mizushima) “Culture Experience Plan”.

151
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:04,604
(Minseok) This is an accommodation plan that combines the cultures of other countries and Japan.

152
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:06,106
>>Yes.

153
00:10:06,173 --> 00:10:08,108
(Minseok) While interacting with customers as a bellman→

154
00:10:08,175 --> 00:10:10,110
I want to go on a trip abroad →

155
00:10:10,177 --> 00:10:13,613
I have heard that there are language and distance barriers.

156
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,116
So while I was in Tokyo→

157
00:10:16,183 --> 00:10:19,119
This is a project where you can easily experience the culture of another country.

158
00:10:19,186 --> 00:10:23,123
First, I thought of a plan for South Korea, where our head office is also located.

159
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:26,626
>> I see, that might be a good idea.

160
00:10:26,693 --> 00:10:31,131
No, my wife and daughter already love Korean culture.

161
00:10:31,198 --> 00:10:33,633
(Minseok) Oh, and one more thing. >> Ah, yes.

162
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:35,635
(Minseok) I live near this hotel →

163
00:10:35,702 --> 00:10:38,638
We have also come up with a special plan for local people.

164
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:41,141
>> Local people? (Minseok) Yes.

165
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:45,145
People who live near this area usually do not stay at this hotel.

166
00:10:45,212 --> 00:10:47,147
But to those people→

167
00:10:47,214 --> 00:10:50,150
Please use this hotel as if it were your second home →

168
00:10:50,217 --> 00:10:52,652
I think that will be a great strength.

169
00:10:52,719 --> 00:10:56,657
>> Ha! I'm short on time so here it is.

170
00:10:56,723 --> 00:10:59,159
(Minseok) Ah, there's more. >> Huh? (Minseok) Next page.

171
00:10:59,226 --> 00:11:01,228
>> Ah yes, please wait a moment.

172
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:06,099
(Momoko) Yes, thank you.

173
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:08,602
(Yusuke) Take a breath.

174
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:12,105
(Yusuke) Spit it out. >> Huh~ What do you think? teacher.

175
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:14,608
Yeah, it's much better now.

176
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:18,612
Oh, is that so? Wow! Ahaha, it’s true! It’s true!

177
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:21,181
Ahahaha it got better.

178
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:26,620
yeah? what up?

179
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:30,190
I was wondering what to do.

180
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:35,629
(Yusuke) The teacher is not getting well →

181
00:11:35,695 --> 00:11:39,633
If we can't come here anymore →

182
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:42,202
What should I do?

183
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:49,142
I'm sorry.

184
00:11:49,209 --> 00:11:52,712
Yeah, I made you worry.

185
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:58,151
(Takuto) Hey, Yusuke! Sort it out quickly.

186
00:11:58,218 --> 00:12:00,654
Today's my special plate.

187
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:03,156
(Yusuke) Yeah! (Takuto) Yes.

188
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:06,093
Alright, it's curry...

189
00:12:06,159 --> 00:12:08,595
(Peach) Dean.

190
00:12:08,662 --> 00:12:10,597
>> It's okay, it's okay.

191
00:12:10,664 --> 00:12:13,600
Hey Momo-chan. (Momoko) Yes.

192
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:16,603
>> Let's not be sad until the end.

193
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:22,109
Let's make lots of fun memories with everyone.

194
00:12:22,175 --> 00:12:24,611
(Momoko) Yes.

195
00:12:24,678 --> 00:12:28,115
(Child) Hey, it looks delicious, right?

196
00:12:28,181 --> 00:12:29,616
(Kazami) Whoa...

197
00:12:29,683 --> 00:12:31,618
(Takuto) Boom!

198
00:12:31,685 --> 00:12:33,620
(Yusuke) What? this.

199
00:12:33,687 --> 00:12:35,622
(Takuto) I~!

200
00:12:35,689 --> 00:12:37,624
(Yusuke) Huh, something is strange.

201
00:12:37,691 --> 00:12:39,626
(Takuto) Huh? (Child) Minseok is better.

202
00:12:39,693 --> 00:12:43,130
Minseok-san is better. (Takuto) Hey, don't say that.

203
00:12:43,196 --> 00:12:45,632
All right, all right, here's the jelly.

204
00:12:45,699 --> 00:12:48,635
(Mika) Minseok-san, are you still working?

205
00:12:48,702 --> 00:12:50,137
(Momoko) Maybe so.

206
00:12:50,203 --> 00:12:54,207
>> It's a shame, since it's been a long time since I've been to a children's cafeteria.

207
00:13:01,214 --> 00:13:03,150
(Minseok) What do you think?

208
00:13:03,216 --> 00:13:05,585
>>Yes.

209
00:13:05,652 --> 00:13:09,089
Now, would you like to forward this information to the head office?

210
00:13:09,156 --> 00:13:11,591
(Minseok) I will create the translation data immediately.

211
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:14,161
(Sound of keyboard hitting)

212
00:13:15,662 --> 00:13:21,168
(Sound of keyboard hitting)

213
00:13:24,171 --> 00:13:26,606
(click sound) (transmission sound)

214
00:13:26,673 --> 00:13:28,608
(Minseok) Ha.

215
00:13:28,675 --> 00:13:38,118
♪～

216
00:13:38,185 --> 00:13:40,120
(Minseok) Oh, I'm home.

217
00:13:40,187 --> 00:13:42,122
(Momoko) Welcome back.

218
00:13:42,189 --> 00:13:44,124
(Minseok) That Momoko-san. (Momoko) Ah, Takuto.

219
00:13:44,191 --> 00:13:46,193
(Takuto) Huh?

220
00:13:49,196 --> 00:13:52,132
(Takuto) Oh, welcome back, Minseok. (Minseok) I'm home.

221
00:13:52,199 --> 00:13:55,135
(Momoko) Please clean up the sign outside.

222
00:13:55,202 --> 00:13:57,137
(Takuto) Yes.

223
00:13:57,204 --> 00:14:00,207
(Momoko) Well then, thank you for your hard work.

224
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:05,645
(Sound of door opening and closing)

225
00:14:08,148 --> 00:14:12,586
(Takuto) Huh... Go after Minchok and make up with him.

226
00:14:12,652 --> 00:14:14,588
You had a fight, right?

227
00:14:14,654 --> 00:14:17,090
(Minseok) Ah, no.

228
00:14:17,157 --> 00:14:19,092
(Takuto) Isn't it a fight?

229
00:14:19,159 --> 00:14:21,161
Then why?

230
00:14:25,665 --> 00:14:29,603
(Takuto) If you're worried, talk to us. We're friends.

231
00:14:29,669 --> 00:14:31,671
Na chingu.

232
00:14:37,611 --> 00:14:39,546
(Takuto) Do you want to break up? That guy?

233
00:14:39,613 --> 00:14:42,549
(Minseok) Yes. (Takuto) Why?

234
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:47,587
(Minseok) I want to focus on my work and dreams.

235
00:14:47,654 --> 00:14:51,591
(Takuto) Huh? What is that?

236
00:14:51,658 --> 00:14:54,160
(Minseok) Please. (Takuto) Thank you.

237
00:14:56,162 --> 00:15:00,600
(Minseok) I know that Momoko-san is worried about the clinic.

238
00:15:00,667 --> 00:15:06,106
I want to be by your side when you're worried.

239
00:15:06,172 --> 00:15:07,607
but….

240
00:15:07,674 --> 00:15:10,677
(Takuto) Did someone say to you that you can do your best alone?

241
00:15:12,679 --> 00:15:14,114
(Minseok) Yes.

242
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,683
(Takuto) No, what is that?

243
00:15:19,686 --> 00:15:24,624
(Takuto) For Momoko, being a doctor is more important than anything else.

244
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:28,628
I think I've sacrificed a lot of things up until now.

245
00:15:28,695 --> 00:15:32,632
When I was a student, I was busy with studying and part-time jobs →

246
00:15:32,699 --> 00:15:36,069
I don't have any time to play with my friends.

247
00:15:36,136 --> 00:15:41,641
There were some guys who looked like boyfriends, but they just disappeared naturally.

248
00:15:44,144 --> 00:15:48,581
But Momoko after meeting Mincheok →

249
00:15:48,648 --> 00:15:53,586
Smiling so much and being so excited →

250
00:15:53,653 --> 00:15:59,159
It's the first time I've seen you look so happy.

251
00:16:01,161 --> 00:16:03,096
For Momoko →

252
00:16:03,163 --> 00:16:06,666
I thought Mincheok was really special.

253
00:16:09,169 --> 00:16:11,671
I've been watching him for a long time, so I understand.

254
00:16:16,676 --> 00:16:21,614
(Takuto) There's some reason why we have to break up →

255
00:16:21,681 --> 00:16:23,683
There must have been something else.

256
00:16:30,190 --> 00:16:33,126
(Takuto) Come on, eat something sweet to cheer yourself up!

257
00:16:33,193 --> 00:16:36,062
This is a jelly brought to me by my parents.

258
00:16:36,129 --> 00:16:38,064
I also saved some for Mincheok.

259
00:16:38,131 --> 00:16:40,567
(Minseok) Ah, itadakimasu.

260
00:16:40,633 --> 00:16:42,569
(Takuto) Please, please.

261
00:16:42,635 --> 00:16:45,071
My mother would be sad if she gave me something→

262
00:16:45,138 --> 00:16:47,574
You'll call me right away.

263
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:50,076
He said, ``Give it to everyone here.''

264
00:16:50,143 --> 00:16:52,579
(Minseok) Isn't it because you want to see Takuto's face?

265
00:16:52,645 --> 00:16:55,648
(Takuto) No, no, I'm just running an errand...

266
00:16:58,151 --> 00:17:02,088
Well, it's a blessing.

267
00:17:02,155 --> 00:17:04,157
(Minseok) It's delicious.

268
00:17:08,661 --> 00:17:13,166
(Takuto) Have you been able to visit your parents' graves since you came back to Japan?

269
00:17:14,667 --> 00:17:17,604
(Minseok) I don't know where the grave is.

270
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:20,106
(Takuto) Don't you understand?

271
00:17:20,173 --> 00:17:22,609
(Minseok) I haven't heard anything from my Korean father either.

272
00:17:22,675 --> 00:17:26,613
I've always wanted to go.

273
00:17:26,679 --> 00:17:29,182
(Takuto) Don't you have any clues?

274
00:17:30,683 --> 00:17:33,119
(Minseok) Yes.

275
00:17:33,186 --> 00:17:35,555
(Takuto) I see.

276
00:17:35,622 --> 00:17:39,058
>> Ah! You did a great job today.

277
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:42,061
(Momoko) Thank you for your hard work. I'll leave you some tea.

278
00:17:42,128 --> 00:17:44,063
>> Ah, thank you.

279
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:47,634
(Momoko) Hey, why did you drink so much yesterday?

280
00:17:49,135 --> 00:17:52,639
>> [Will Momoko be able to be happy?] ]

281
00:17:54,641 --> 00:17:58,578
It's just that it's more fun because I'm with Taku-chan.

282
00:17:58,645 --> 00:18:01,147
(Momoko) Hmm, I see.

283
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:07,153
>> Hey Momoko. (Momoko) Huh?

284
00:18:11,658 --> 00:18:14,093
>> I'm an idiot.

285
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:18,097
Momoko has become so splendid.

286
00:18:18,164 --> 00:18:19,599
(Momoko) Huh?

287
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:22,101
>> Not yet in my mind →

288
00:18:22,168 --> 00:18:26,673
Right in front of Momoko, who was waddling after me.

289
00:18:31,177 --> 00:18:33,680
I have a lot of unnecessary worries.

290
00:18:38,184 --> 00:18:40,186
Be happy.

291
00:18:42,188 --> 00:18:46,192
That's my only request from my sister.

292
00:18:47,694 --> 00:18:50,630
Fufufu…｡

293
00:18:50,697 --> 00:18:53,132
Good night then.

294
00:18:53,199 --> 00:18:55,702
(Momoko) Good night. >> Yeah.

295
00:18:57,203 --> 00:19:00,707
(Sound of door opening and closing)

296
00:19:10,717 --> 00:19:20,660
♪～

297
00:19:20,727 --> 00:19:22,729
(Minseok) Hello.

298
00:19:27,734 --> 00:19:29,736
(Minseok) Inri-san.

299
00:19:32,238 --> 00:19:34,240
Let me ask you directly.

300
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,678
Haven't you met Momoko?

301
00:19:40,980 --> 00:19:43,917
>> Why?

302
00:19:43,983 --> 00:19:45,919
Did Momoko say something?

303
00:19:45,985 --> 00:19:48,922
(Minseok) First, answer my question.

304
00:19:48,988 --> 00:19:53,426
>> You're probably more worried about the hotel in Tokyo.

305
00:19:53,493 --> 00:19:55,428
I told you this the other day.

306
00:19:55,495 --> 00:19:59,933
There is a way to help both you and the hotel in Tokyo.

307
00:19:59,999 --> 00:20:02,936
(Minseok) Mr. Eri. >> That's right→

308
00:20:03,002 --> 00:20:08,441
You will marry me and become the son-in-law of the Shinkai family.

309
00:20:08,508 --> 00:20:10,443
(Minseok) Huh?

310
00:20:10,510 --> 00:20:13,446
>> Then hotels in Tokyo will be protected →

311
00:20:13,513 --> 00:20:17,517
You can put your skills as a hotelier to use at our house.

312
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:23,022
(Minseok) What are you talking about?

313
00:20:25,024 --> 00:20:27,460
What happened to your marriage with your brother?

314
00:20:27,527 --> 00:20:29,963
>> I refuse.

315
00:20:30,029 --> 00:20:34,033
I'm buying your skills as a hotel manager.

316
00:20:35,969 --> 00:20:38,404
You can grow the Shinkai Group →

317
00:20:38,471 --> 00:20:40,974
It can make me shine.

318
00:20:42,475 --> 00:20:46,980
Marrying me is a business.

319
00:20:51,484 --> 00:20:54,420
(Minseok) Maybe that →

320
00:20:54,487 --> 00:20:56,923
Did you talk to Momoko?

321
00:20:56,990 --> 00:21:01,494
>> Well, how was it?

322
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,937
(Minseok) Okay, let's go.

323
00:21:11,004 --> 00:21:13,439
>>Wait.

324
00:21:13,506 --> 00:21:16,943
The story isn't over yet.

325
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:19,445
Your mother-in-law accused you of embezzlement →

326
00:21:19,512 --> 00:21:21,447
Apparently they are preparing to sue.

327
00:21:21,514 --> 00:21:24,017
(Minseok) I haven't done anything.

328
00:21:25,518 --> 00:21:28,955
When you go to court, you just have to prove your innocence.

329
00:21:29,022 --> 00:21:31,958
>> Hwang Geum will bring together the best lawyers to take on the lawsuit.

330
00:21:32,025 --> 00:21:33,960
(Minseok) There is nothing stronger than innocence.

331
00:21:34,027 --> 00:21:35,895
>>It's sweet.

332
00:21:35,962 --> 00:21:38,898
Those people→

333
00:21:38,965 --> 00:21:42,402
If you want to win, make white things black.

334
00:21:42,468 --> 00:21:45,905
You have no chance of winning.

335
00:21:45,972 --> 00:21:48,908
You are burdened with huge debts and

336
00:21:48,975 --> 00:21:51,978
I can no longer work at a hotel.

337
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:58,918
That clinic will also be a nuisance.

338
00:21:58,985 --> 00:22:02,422
He was harboring someone who was being sued for embezzlement →

339
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:07,427
If rumors are spread, I won't be able to survive.

340
00:22:07,493 --> 00:22:09,996
I'm sure there will be a children's cafeteria too.

341
00:22:11,998 --> 00:22:16,936
But if you marry me, your mother-in-law will also be discouraged from filing lawsuits.

342
00:22:17,003 --> 00:22:21,507
They probably want to avoid a hostile relationship with the Shinkai Group.

343
00:22:23,009 --> 00:22:25,445
Got it?

344
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:29,015
There is no place for you but next to me.

345
00:22:32,018 --> 00:22:35,888
Hurry up and pack your things and come to my place.

346
00:22:35,955 --> 00:22:38,458
Before it's too late.

347
00:22:49,635 --> 00:22:52,071
(Mika) [Welcome back]

348
00:22:52,138 --> 00:22:55,074
[Oh, welcome back] (Momoko) [Welcome back]

349
00:22:55,141 --> 00:23:05,084
♪～

350
00:23:05,151 --> 00:23:09,589
(Momoko) [I hope it becomes a place where children can smile.]

351
00:23:09,655 --> 00:23:14,160
[This is a very important place for me]

352
00:23:19,665 --> 00:23:21,167
(Sound of turning on the light)

353
00:23:22,668 --> 00:23:25,104
(Minseok) [Please wait a moment]

354
00:23:25,171 --> 00:24:08,080
♪～

355
00:24:08,147 --> 00:24:11,584
>> Good morning, Minseok.

356
00:24:11,651 --> 00:24:13,653
(Minseok) Good morning.

357
00:24:20,159 --> 00:24:24,163
>> There's something to talk about.

358
00:24:25,665 --> 00:24:27,667
(Minseok) Yes.

359
00:24:33,673 --> 00:24:36,609
>> Korean

360
00:25:01,133 --> 00:25:04,637
(Sound of door opening and closing)

361
00:25:37,103 --> 00:25:39,105
(Kyonhua) Ah~!

362
00:25:41,107 --> 00:25:44,544
(Momoko) Yeah, it's normal. Let's reduce the medication a little.

363
00:25:44,610 --> 00:25:47,113
(Patient) Thank you. (Momoko) Yes.

364
00:25:49,115 --> 00:25:51,117
Next person please.

365
00:25:52,618 --> 00:25:54,053
Oh, Director.

366
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:59,058
>> Now that the patient is out, I think I'll have my blood pressure measured as well.

367
00:25:59,125 --> 00:26:01,560
(Momoko) Please.

368
00:26:01,627 --> 00:26:03,629
yes.

369
00:26:05,631 --> 00:26:07,566
Director. >> Huh?

370
00:26:07,633 --> 00:26:12,138
(Momoko) From now on, please don't push yourself too hard.

371
00:26:13,639 --> 00:26:16,075
>>Yes.

372
00:26:16,142 --> 00:26:18,077
Hey Momo-chan.

373
00:26:18,144 --> 00:26:19,578
(Momoko) Yes.

374
00:26:19,645 --> 00:26:21,647
>> This morning...

375
00:26:25,651 --> 00:26:29,088
(Minseok) [Click here→

376
00:26:29,155 --> 00:26:31,157
I'm leaving]

377
00:26:35,661 --> 00:26:40,666
(Minseok) [Thank you for your help so far]

378
00:26:42,668 --> 00:26:47,673
>> [I don't mind if you stay forever]

379
00:26:50,676 --> 00:26:54,680
(Minseok) [Thank you very much]

380
00:27:03,189 --> 00:27:05,124
>> [Minseok]

381
00:27:05,191 --> 00:27:09,128
(Minseok) [Here is →

382
00:27:09,195 --> 00:27:14,633
This is an important place that has created a place for me.]

383
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:20,139
[I'll never forget that]

384
00:27:20,206 --> 00:27:23,642
>> [Hey Minseok-kun→

385
00:27:23,709 --> 00:27:27,713
What about this, Momo-chan? ]

386
00:27:29,715 --> 00:27:31,650
(Minseok) [No]

387
00:27:31,717 --> 00:27:34,220
>> [I see]

388
00:27:38,657 --> 00:27:41,093
[It's a talisman]

389
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:45,164
[So that Minseok doesn't get lost]

390
00:27:47,166 --> 00:27:52,605
[So that I can come back here again]

391
00:27:52,671 --> 00:28:04,617
♪～

392
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:06,685
(Minseok) [Thank you]

393
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:12,124
(Kazami) Why do I have to leave here?→

394
00:28:12,191 --> 00:28:14,693
I couldn't ask why.

395
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:22,201
I feel like I need to step into something.

396
00:28:25,704 --> 00:28:27,139
Momo-chan.

397
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:29,141
(Momoko) Blood pressure is normal.

398
00:28:29,208 --> 00:28:31,143
(Sound of removing blood pressure cuff)

399
00:28:31,210 --> 00:28:33,145
(Momoko) Good.

400
00:28:33,212 --> 00:29:09,181
♪～

401
00:29:17,690 --> 00:29:19,692
(sound of door opening)

402
00:29:22,194 --> 00:29:25,131
(Momoko) Ah...｡

403
00:29:25,197 --> 00:29:27,199
Mr. Minseok.

404
00:29:29,702 --> 00:29:33,205
(Minseok) Sorry, I was away.

405
00:29:35,641 --> 00:29:38,577
Ah, ah…｡

406
00:29:38,644 --> 00:29:41,147
I forgot something.

407
00:29:42,648 --> 00:29:44,150
(Momoko) No.

408
00:29:49,655 --> 00:29:51,590
(Momoko) That.

409
00:29:51,657 --> 00:29:53,659
(Minseok) Yes.

410
00:29:56,662 --> 00:30:00,666
(Momoko) Are you really leaving?

411
00:30:06,172 --> 00:30:08,174
(Minseok) Yes.

412
00:30:13,179 --> 00:30:15,114
(Minseok) Momoko-san.

413
00:30:15,181 --> 00:30:17,183
(Momoko) How are you?

414
00:30:20,186 --> 00:30:22,188
(sound of door opening)

415
00:30:25,191 --> 00:30:29,695
(Sound of door opening and closing)

416
00:30:32,698 --> 00:30:34,633
(Momoko) Ha.

417
00:30:34,700 --> 00:31:08,167
♪～

418
00:31:12,671 --> 00:32:27,112
♪～

419
00:32:27,179 --> 00:32:42,628
(cry)

420
00:32:49,068 --> 00:32:51,003
>> Momo-chan. (Momoko) Welcome back.

421
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:53,505
>> Are you still here?

422
00:32:53,572 --> 00:32:57,009
(Momoko) I was waiting for the director.

423
00:32:57,076 --> 00:33:00,579
>> What? what happened?

424
00:33:09,088 --> 00:33:14,593
(Momoko) If it wasn't for this, I wouldn't be where I am today.

425
00:33:16,595 --> 00:33:21,600
That's why I want to protect this place.

426
00:33:25,104 --> 00:33:27,106
(Momoko) I don't want to give up yet.

427
00:33:29,608 --> 00:33:31,610
>> Momo-chan.

428
00:33:33,112 --> 00:33:36,482
(Momoko) Minseok feels the same way.

429
00:33:36,548 --> 00:33:55,501
♪～

430
00:33:55,567 --> 00:33:58,570
>> It's a tough thing to protect.

431
00:34:03,075 --> 00:34:08,080
(Momoko) It's difficult, but it's important.

432
00:34:11,583 --> 00:34:14,520
(Momoko) That's why the director also →

433
00:34:14,586 --> 00:34:17,022
Haven't you been protecting it all this time?

434
00:34:17,089 --> 00:34:32,538
♪～

435
00:34:32,604 --> 00:34:36,108
>> No more...

436
00:34:42,614 --> 00:34:47,052
Thank you, Momo-chan.

437
00:34:47,119 --> 00:35:13,145
♪～

438
00:35:17,649 --> 00:35:19,585
Yes, this document is fine.

439
00:35:19,651 --> 00:35:21,587
(Momoko) Thank you very much.

440
00:35:21,653 --> 00:35:25,090
Oh, and... I'm sorry.

441
00:35:25,157 --> 00:35:27,159
Please read it.

442
00:35:32,164 --> 00:35:34,166
(Momoko) Thank you very much.

443
00:35:37,102 --> 00:35:39,037
(Takuto) Huh?

444
00:35:39,104 --> 00:35:40,539
(Momoko) Yay!

445
00:35:40,606 --> 00:35:42,541
(Takuto) Oh!

446
00:35:42,608 --> 00:35:45,544
I see. (Momoko) Yeah.

447
00:35:45,611 --> 00:35:48,046
I was able to apply for a grant →

448
00:35:48,113 --> 00:35:50,549
I think I'll try a little harder.

449
00:35:50,616 --> 00:35:52,551
(Takuto) Ha...

450
00:35:52,618 --> 00:35:54,553
(Momoko) I'm sorry I tried to throw you around.

451
00:35:54,620 --> 00:35:57,556
Regarding the satellite incident, Takuto was doing his best.

452
00:35:57,623 --> 00:36:01,059
(Takuto) No, that's not it...

453
00:36:01,126 --> 00:36:03,562
(Momoko) Huh?

454
00:36:03,629 --> 00:36:06,565
(Takuto) I'm so relieved!

455
00:36:06,632 --> 00:36:08,567
(Momoko) Huh?

456
00:36:08,634 --> 00:36:12,070
(Takuto) No, well, by making Kazami Clinic a satellite →

457
00:36:12,137 --> 00:36:14,573
I'm sure a lot of good things happened.

458
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:18,076
Neither the director nor Momoko thought about management →

459
00:36:18,143 --> 00:36:20,078
I can face the patient.

460
00:36:20,145 --> 00:36:25,150
By being closely connected with us, we can provide the latest medical care.

461
00:36:27,653 --> 00:36:30,589
But →

462
00:36:30,656 --> 00:36:35,093
After all, what would we do without a children's cafeteria?

463
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:38,530
Taking away the children's place.

464
00:36:38,597 --> 00:36:41,033
(Peach) Takuto.

465
00:36:41,099 --> 00:36:43,035
(Takuto) Later…｡

466
00:36:43,101 --> 00:36:45,037
(Momoko) Yes.

467
00:36:45,103 --> 00:36:47,539
(Takuto) I don't want the kids to mess with me over there →

468
00:36:47,606 --> 00:36:50,542
It was the best healing experience. (Momoko) Huh?

469
00:36:50,609 --> 00:36:53,045
(Takuto) That's why I'm really glad you declined.

470
00:36:53,111 --> 00:36:56,048
(Momoko) Hehehe what? that.

471
00:36:56,114 --> 00:37:01,053
(Takuto) If there was a children's cafeteria, I would be able to eat Momoko's delicate dishes again.

472
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:04,122
(Momoko) Don't say it's subtle. (Takuto) Hehehe...｡

473
00:37:06,625 --> 00:37:08,060
(Momoko) You know.

474
00:37:08,126 --> 00:37:10,062
(Takuto) Huh?

475
00:37:10,128 --> 00:37:15,634
(Momoko) About the clinic, Minseok-san supported me.

476
00:37:17,135 --> 00:37:19,071
(Takuto) I see.

477
00:37:19,137 --> 00:37:21,640
Well, I have to thank Mincheok.

478
00:37:23,141 --> 00:37:24,643
(Momoko) Yes.

479
00:37:26,144 --> 00:37:30,082
(Takuto) I mean, don't you guys talk too much to me about everything?

480
00:37:30,148 --> 00:37:32,584
(Momoko) Huh? Is that so?

481
00:37:32,651 --> 00:37:35,087
(Takuto) Well, I guess it can't be helped.

482
00:37:35,153 --> 00:37:38,090
I'm the one between you two.

483
00:37:41,093 --> 00:37:43,028
(Momoko) Ching? what? that.

484
00:37:43,095 --> 00:37:45,530
(Takuto) That's a lie. Wait a minute.

485
00:37:45,597 --> 00:37:47,532
You should study Korean.

486
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:50,602
(Momoko) Oh, it's Korean. (Takuto) It's Korean, Ching.

487
00:37:58,610 --> 00:38:00,612
>> Han River Do you remember?

488
00:38:03,115 --> 00:38:06,051
Do you miss Korea?

489
00:38:06,118 --> 00:38:08,053
Even though I was kicked out→

490
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:11,623
Of course I spent 23 years there.

491
00:38:14,126 --> 00:38:16,561
(Minseok) For me→

492
00:38:16,628 --> 00:38:20,565
Thank you for thinking about everything.

493
00:38:20,632 --> 00:38:24,069
>> Let's have our wedding in both Japan and Korea.

494
00:38:24,136 --> 00:38:26,571
Your mother-in-law and brother-in-law probably won't be attending.

495
00:38:26,638 --> 00:38:28,073
It's okay.

496
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:32,144
My guests alone will be enough to make it a grand start.

497
00:38:35,147 --> 00:38:39,584
(Minseok) But I won't marry you.

498
00:38:41,086 --> 00:38:45,023
>> Eh, why?

499
00:38:45,090 --> 00:38:48,527
Even though I said I would help you.

500
00:38:48,593 --> 00:38:52,030
(Minseok) I want to protect the people I care about with my power.

501
00:38:52,097 --> 00:38:55,534
>> I can't do it. I've lost everything. What can you do?

502
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:59,538
I can protect the hotel and your future.

503
00:38:59,604 --> 00:39:02,040
(Minseok) I don't need your help.

504
00:39:02,107 --> 00:39:04,543
>> What are you talking about?

505
00:39:04,609 --> 00:39:09,047
If you marry me, you won't have to suffer at all.

506
00:39:09,114 --> 00:39:11,550
You can do the work you like at Shinkai Group.

507
00:39:11,616 --> 00:39:13,618
You can live without any inconvenience.

508
00:39:16,121 --> 00:39:19,057
We can make each other shine→

509
00:39:19,124 --> 00:39:22,627
You can become the best partner that everyone envy.

510
00:39:25,130 --> 00:39:29,067
(Minseok) The best partner for me is →

